<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="15" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Austro-Hungarian
                                    Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lenox,
                                        Mass.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-01"><hi rend="italic">July 1,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Following instructions received, I have the honor to present herewith to
                            the Government of the United States the most sincere condolences of the
                            Imperial and Royal Government on the occasion of the deeply regretted
                            death of His Excellency the Hon. John Hay, Secretary of State.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Giskra.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>